To use App Autoscaler, you must create an instance of the App Autoscaler service and bind it to an app.
Follow the procedure in this section to configure App Autoscaler after you create the service instance.
See [Scaling an Application Using App Autoscaler](http://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/appsman-services/autoscaler/using-autoscaler.html) for more information.

1. Click **App Autoscaler**.

    <%= image_tag("app-autoscaler.png") %>

1. For **Autoscaler Instance Count**, enter a number of instances for the App Autoscaler service.

1. For **Autoscaler API Instance Count**, enter a number of instances for the App Autoscaler API.

1. For **Metric Collection Interval**, specify the number of seconds of metric collection data that autoscaler evaluates when it makes scaling decisions.
The minimum interval is 15 seconds and the maximum interval is 120 seconds.

1. For **Scaling Interval**, enter a number in seconds that determines how frequently the autoscaler evaluates an application for scaling.
The minimum interval is 15 seconds and the maximum interval is 120 seconds.

1. Click **Save**.
